content:
great idea, great realisation , this attraction is a definite must for children but also adults. I had never seen some of those animals despite visiting many zoos in various continents. Giant otters of the amazon and manatees but also Gharial and those mississippi paddelfishes.
The size of the aquariums and the clever viewing platforms thanks to modern technology are so impressive you could easily spend hours there.
Too warm? go to the panda dome to cool down or the amazon flooded forest;
Raining? no worries, it is all covered
I suggest to start your day at the zoo, then do the river safari when it is really hot, and finish the day with the night safari;
Travelling with small children? do not miss the tour where they bring animals for children to touch (snakes, lizard, etc)
